concept_explanation.amortized:
**Amortized Analysis — cost averaged across many operations:**

```java
// ArrayList.add(e) — amortized O(1):
// When internal array is full, it doubles (capacity × 2)
// Copy all existing elements: O(n) operation
// But resizing happens rarely — every n adds triggers one O(n) resize
// Total cost for n adds: n × O(1) + log(n) × O(n) = O(n)
// Per-operation amortized: O(n) / n = O(1)

// Visualization:
// Add 1:  [1] — capacity 1, no resize needed
// Add 2:  [1,_] full! resize to 2, copy 1 element → [1,2]
// Add 3:  [1,2,_,_] full! resize to 4, copy 2 elements → [1,2,3,_]
// Add 4:  [1,2,3,4] — no resize
// Add 5:  full! resize to 8, copy 4 elements → [1,2,3,4,5,_,_,_]
// Resizes happen at n=1,2,4,8,16... costs: 1+2+4+8+...+n = 2n = O(n)
// Total: O(n) for n inserts → O(1) amortized per insert
```

